# Deployment Instructions for GitHub Pages

This guide explains how to deploy your Angular project to GitHub Pages using the docs folder.

## 1. Configure Angular Build Output
- Edit `angular.json`:
  - Set `outputPath` to `docs` under the build options.

## 2. Build the Project
- Run:
  ```
  ng build --configuration production
  ```
- The build output will be placed in the `docs` folder.

## 3. Move Build Files to Docs Root
- If Angular outputs files to a subfolder (like `docs/browser`), move all files to the root of `docs`:
  - On Windows PowerShell:
    ```
    Move-Item -Path 'docs/browser/*' -Destination 'docs/' -Force
    Remove-Item -Path 'docs/browser' -Recurse -Force
    ```

## 4. Update Base Href
- Edit `docs/index.html`:
  - Change `<base href="/">` to `<base href="/porsche-website-deployCheck/">` (replace with your repo name).

## 5. Commit and Push Changes
- Add, commit, and push your changes:
  ```
  git add .
  git commit -m "Deploy to GitHub Pages"
  git push origin main
  ```

## 6. Configure GitHub Pages
- Go to your repository settings on GitHub.
- Under "Pages", set the source to the `docs` folder on the `main` branch.

## 7. Verify Deployment
- Visit `https://<your-username>.github.io/<your-repo>/`.
- The site should load with all assets and styles.

## Troubleshooting
- Ensure all build files (including `index.html` and stylesheets) are in the root of `docs`.
- Make sure the base href matches your repository name.
- Clear browser cache if assets do not load.

